bay|1999}}\u2013{{nbay|2004}}\n*'''Only NBA player to average at least 20 points, 10 rebounds and 4 assists per game for 9 consecutive seasons''': {{nbay|1998}}\u2013{{nbay|2006}}\n*'''Seasons leading the league in defensive rebounds''': 5 ({{nbay|2002}}\u2013{{nbay|2006}})\n**Broken by [[Dwight Howard]] ({{nbay|2007}}\u2013{{nbay|2012}})\n*'''Consecutive seasons leading the league in defensive rebounds''': 5 ({{nbay|2002}}\u2013{{nbay|2006}})\n**Broken by [[Dwight Howard]] ({{nbay|2007}}\u2013{{nbay|2012}})\n*'''First NBA player to win the NBA Player of the Month Award four times in a single season''': [[2003\u201304 NBA season|2003\u201304 season]]\n**Also achieved by [[LeBron James]], who has achieved this twice\n* '''Third NBA player to lead his team in all five major statistics (points, rebounds, assists, steals, blocks) in the same season''': Minnesota Timberwolves, {{nbay|2002}}\n**Also achieved by [[Dave Cowens]] (Boston Celtics, {{nbay|1977}}), [[Scottie Pippen]] (Chicago Bulls, {{nbay|1994}}), [[LeBron James]] (Cleveland Cavaliers, {{nbay|2008}}), and [[Giannis Antetokounmpo]] (Milwaukee Bucks, {{nbay|2016}})\n*'''Tied for [[List of National Basketball Association seasons played leaders|the second most seasons played in the NBA]]''': 21 seasons\n**Also achieved by [[Robert Parish]] and [[Kevin Willis]]\n*'''Achievements''':\n*'''NBA champion''': 2008\n*'''Olympic gold medal''': 2000\n*'''[[NBA Most Valuable Player Award|NBA Most Valuable Player]]''': 2004\n*'''[[NBA Defensive Player of the Year Award|NBA Defensive Player of the Year]]''': 2008\n*'''[[NBA All-Star Game Most Valuable Player Award|NBA All-Star Game MVP]]''': 2003\n*'''15-time [[NBA All-Star]]''': 1997\u20132011, 2013\n**Selected to 14 consecutive All-Star teams ([[1997 NBA All-Star Game|1997]]\u2013[[2011 NBA All-Star Game|2011]]) (no game in 1999 due to lockout)\n**Selected in [[2008 NBA All-Star Game|2008]], but did not play due to injury\n*'''9-time [[All-NBA Team|All-NBA]] selection''':\n**'''First Team''': 2000, 2003, 2004, 2008\n**'''Second Team''': 2001, 2002, 2005\n**'''Third Team''': 1999, 2007\n*'''12-time All-Defensive''':\n**'''First Team''': 2000\u20132005, 2008\u20132009, 2011\n**'''Second Team''': 2006\u20132007, 2012\n*'''NBA [[NBA All-Rookie Team|All-Rookie]] selection''':\n**'''Second team: 1996'''\n*'''J. Walter Kennedy Citizenship Award''': 2006\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Sports}}\n* [[List of NBA All-Stars]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association career games played leaders]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association career scoring leaders]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association career rebounding leaders]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association career assists leaders]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association career steals leaders]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association career blocks leaders]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association career turnovers leaders]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association career free throw scoring leaders]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association career minutes played leaders]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association career playoff rebounding leaders]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association career playoff blocks leaders]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association annual rebounding leaders]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association seasons played leaders]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Kevin Garnett}}\n{{basketballstats|nba=kevin_garnett|bbr=g/garneke01}}\n*{{facebook|kevingarnett}}\n\n{{Navboxes|list1=\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-ach}}\n{{Succession box| title=[[Illinois Mr. Basketball]] Award Winner | before=[[Jarrod Gee]] | years=1995| after=[[Ronnie Fields]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{2020 Basketball HOF}}\n{{Mr. Basketball USA}}\n{{USA Today National Basketball Player of the Year}}\n{{1995 NBA Draft}}\n{{NBA MVP's}}\n{{NBA Defensive Players of the Year}}\n{{NBA All-Star Game MVP Awar